multiple_choice_question.text: For N=1, what is the effect of the lowest three Virasoro constraints on the partition function according to Claim 1?
choices: They completely determine the partition function.
They act as shifts on the internal parameters of the partition function.
They have no effect on the partition function.
They transform the partition function into a non-integrable expression.

multiple_choice_question.text: How does Claim 2 generalize the first two Virasoro constraints from N=1 to N>1?
choices: The generalization is straightforward with no modifications.
The partition function is replaced with a more complex function.
Shifts are applied to multiple components in the same direction.
A different type of mathematical relation is used.

multiple_choice_question.text: According to Claim 3, what is the implication of the homogeneity of the first two Virasoro constraints?
choices: They can be combined into a single, more complex constraint.
They impose an additional requirement on the partition function.
They imply a rational relation between specific ratios involving the partition function.
They can be solved explicitly for the partition function.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is the significance of Claim 5 regarding the q-deformation of the model?
choices: The q-deformation breaks the pattern observed in the original model.
The q-deformation necessitates using different mathematical tools.
The overall pattern, including the Virasoro constraints, survives the q-deformation.
The q-deformation simplifies the original model significantly.
